"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"```\\nTo achieve opening to extensions and closing to modifications, that is, to follow the principle of opening and closing, the system needs to be abstracted design, abstraction can be based on abstract classes or interfaces. Generally speaking, a few things need to be done:\\n\\nExpansion is restricted by interface or abstract class, and the boundary of the extension is restricted. Public methods that do not exist in the interface or abstract class are not allowed. That is, the extension must add concrete implementations instead of changing concrete methods.\\nParameter types and reference objects try to use interfaces or abstract classes instead of implementation classes, so as to ensure that the abstraction layer is as stable as possible.\\nGenerally, the abstract module design is completed (for example, the interface method has been finalized), and the definition of the interface or abstract method is not allowed to be modified.\\n```\",\"timestamp\":1636433538,\"title\":\"How to achieve openness for extension and closeness for modification\"},\"digest\":\"3XSL7OYDOk0NzZCIo_K0XVWcBzztxWkO2pOyJq2mPYY\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x8fC645e6a176F07395B8f44196d1443772FE9d57\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"QZRQ7gY5Jn-48qIa-AtYm0IM2Dp_mQk7CrD32u5yv7o\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Pi39ZLzMi0BqvyLWy9v2qPY2JVnAcMqh4-AoBP69eN4\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"AyQJ5sDOg8N8PzaEhN9WN0QTbYSzmgrsCYU-nmRYz3No7pFjBFeh_wmtU_YxtkzKEsuHsYF6zafgIMInXHC-1Q\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xea2123da555bddcfd7a799ce3f8a9090d0b2859ad1a71fe17f892210b8a535af05795f1aa2c6c7007ace8c0593705ee96129fae0af65bc0534cb05030c6b38d21b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"QZRQ7gY5Jn-48qIa-AtYm0IM2Dp_mQk7CrD32u5yv7o\\\",\\\"y\\\":\